TURAIF, Jun 21 (APP):Pilgrims with disabilities left Turaif governorate on Wednesday heading to King Abdulaziz Airport in Jeddah to perform this yearâ€™s Hajj rituals, as part of the national initiative launched by the Ministry of Hajj and Umrah in cooperation with the specialized sub-council for the Associations for People with Disabilities.
According to Saudi Press Agency (SPA), the initiative facilitates the Hajj journey for disabled people from all regions of the Kingdom.
